For example: 'T' >>> from datetime import tzinfo, timedelta, datetime >>> class TZ(tzinfo):. """A time zone with an arbitrary, constant -06:39 offset. """. def utcoffset(self, dt):. return timedelta(hours=-6, minutes=-39). >>> datetime(2002, 12, 25, tzinfo=TZ()). isoformat(' ') '2002-12-25 00:00:00-06:39' >>> datetime(2009, 11, 27, microsecond=100, tzinfo=TZ()).
